I always come here after I get off the train from work , the African girl that work there is very sweet  to me. I went there one rainy day after work and this homeless guy was sitting outside of it asking for food , he didn’t ask for my money or anything. So I took him inside and my usual friend was back there and a new face I haven’t seen before an Indian girl. I told him to order whatever he wants and I’ll get it , besides that I ordered me my favorite donut which is the chocolate glaze. He wanted a bagel with cream cheese and a cup of water but was to shy to speak so I told the African girl ( which is my friend ) the order , she then told the Indian girl to make a cup of water because she was just standing there staring. After she made the small cup of water , the homeless guy said ma’am can you add ice to that she goes to say “That’s not for you, it’s for her “. I was so pissed off after that ‼️ I replied with if the cup of water was for me , you still could’ve gave it to him because it’s muggy , water is free and I’m a good person. I wish I would’ve gotten her name , I asked her how dare she decline someone in his predicament a free cup of water. They will not get my money anymore.
